DisplayText: You can't rush storing information in your long term memory. It takes time and repetition and this is a tactic called spaced repetition. So space repetition involves learning something and then after a period of time going back and reviewing it, or even better, actively recalling this information or learning curve, or better yet, labeled. Our forgetting curve is very steep initially. When learning something, however, we go back and actually retrieve it or review it. This curve actually levels out. So how did I actually implement this?
